      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.datarecoverysoftwarehelp.com/?p=534</guid>
      <description>Everyone loves to cherish the golden moments of their lives and in this regard photos play an important role. Today with the inception of digital camera, it has become quite easy to click photos anytime anywhere but with this advancement in the photo technology, preserving a photo is still a matter of concern.&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/data-recovery-software-help/Data_Recovery_Software_Help-Digital_Photo_Recovery_is_still_possible_without_backup.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><!-- p { margin-bottom: 0.21cm; } -->Everyone loves to cherish the golden moments of their lives and in this regard photos play an important role. Today with the inception of digital camera, it has become quite easy to click photos anytime anywhere but with this advancement in the photo technology, preserving a photo is still a matter of concern. However, after the advent of <strong><a href="http://www.stellarinfo.com/digital-media-recovery.htm">photo recovery</a> </strong>software, deleted or lost digital photos are thing of the past. These specialized photo recovery tools use intense algorithms to scan the storage space like memory card, hard disk, etc to recover the photos.</p>
<p>But, before anything else, we must first understand the reasons which lead to digital photo loss:</p>
<ul>
<li>Accidental deletion of photos</li>
<li>Pulling out the memory card while the digital camera is on</li>
<li>Intentional or unintentional formatting of storage device like 	memory card or hard disk of computer</li>
<li>Damage or corruption in the file system of storage device</li>
<li>Rapid clicking of photos which prevents completion of write process</li>
<li>Switching off the digital camera soon after clicking a photograph 	also interrupts the photo write process and thus, leads to photo 	loss</li>
<li>Ignoring the warnings like low battery and memory card full may also 	corrupt the memory card and thus create the situation of photo loss</li>
<li>Erroneous or interrupted read/write process</li>
</ul>
<p>All the above mentioned situations lead to the situation of photo loss. To prevent the loss, it is always recommended to maintain the backup. It is advised to save all your precious photos and videos at multiple locations. However, despite of various precautions measures observed by a user to prevent his/her photos from getting lost there happens some time when user loses his/her precious photos. But, situations of photo loss too can easily be handled through efficient third-party photo recovery software.</p>
<p>Efficient photo recovery software has simple user interface and easy photo recovery steps. All you need to do is to attach the memory card or other affected storage media to your computer, scan the media with the photo recovery software, see the preview of the recoverable photos, and in the end save the recovered photos at your desired location. But, in case you are facing the issue due to memory card corruption then you need to format the card to bring it back to the working condition and then use the above mentioned mechanism to recover the photos.</p>
<p>One of the highly recommended <strong><a href="http://www.stellarinfo.com/digital-media-recovery.htm">photo recovery software</a> </strong>is Stellar Phoenix Photo Recovery. This powerful photo recovery software recovers photos in 3-simple steps, has very intuitive user interface, and is available for Mac and Windows users separately.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
