      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.datarecoverysoftwarehelp.com/?p=530</guid>
      <description>Windows is the mostly used operating system in the world. Around 90% of computer users use Windows operating system as the primary OS in their computers, where as Mac, LINUX and others are able to hold less than 10%. Windows is popular among its users for its advanced features and user-friendly graphical user interfaces. In [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/data-recovery-software-help/Data_Recovery_Software_Help-Deleted_an_Important_file_accidentally_from_your_PC__Dont_worry_Undelete_files_Now.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><!-- p { margin-bottom: 0.21cm; }a:link {  } --><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Windows is the mostly used operating system in the world. Around 90% of computer users use Windows operating system as the primary OS in their computers, where as Mac, LINUX and others are able to hold less than 10%. Windows is popular among its users for its advanced features and user-friendly graphical user interfaces. In true sense, the operating system has been designed, keeping the knowledge level of a non-technical computer user and thus even a novice can use it, without much assistance. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">But, as this simplicity attracts more users, at the same time Windows based systems suffer from data loss problems the most. However, you need not be worried working on it, as there are many efficient Windows recovery software available to retrieve all your lost, deleted or inaccessible data back.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">While working on your PC, accidental deletion, formatting of the hard drive partition is not that uncommon. Everyday, many Windows users lose their valuable data to such problems and think that they can never be able to recover the deleted data again. But, gone are the days, when once you deleted a file could never be retrieved. Now there are many data recovery utilities available, using which you can recover all your deleted or even formatted data back. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">In case of deletion, Windows OS has only removed the entries of the deleted files from the system hard drive. Hence, the files still present in the memory and they will remain in the hard drive memory, until some other files overwrite them. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Thus, if the removed or deleted entries of files can be read, those files can be easily restored in their source locations. <a href="http://www.stellarinfo.com/windows-data-recovery.php">Windows data recovery</a> software are designed with highly advanced algorithms, which able to find out the lost entries of files and successfully recover them back.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">These utilities are also able to recover data from various other data loss instances, such as file system corruption, Windows OS malfunction, virus/malware infection etc. In spite of being powerful, these Windows recovery utilities are completely read-only in their recovery operations and recover lost/inaccessible data, without even modifying their original structure. Moreover, these recovery utilities are designed with simple as well as interactive graphical user interfaces and can be used by any category of Windows users, from experts to the non-technical ones. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">(</span>6H2XXA4R54X3<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">)<br />
</span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
