<p>Valuable files get lost due to various reasons. These reasons include, format or corruption of a hard drive, fatal virus attack, unexpected system shutdown, or software failure. These all are the reasons by which files get lost or become inaccessible. Most of the times, it happens when we delete a file accidentally, we have an option to recover deleted file from the recycle bin. But, at times we fail to recover it if we do double click on recycle bin because file does not present there. Generally, when file once get deleted it goes to the recycle bin folder, but as said earlier many times file found to be absent in the recycle bin folder.</p>
<p>Above stated problem of deletion occurs, when a combination of Shift+Delete key has been used to delete a file. After the use of such combination, file becomes permanently inaccessible. So, situations similar to this can be handled easily with the help of a third party tool. A third party tool is a best fix to recover deleted files again. Before going to do a selection of a third party tool, it is advised to make use of an inbuilt methods.</p>
