      <comments>http://www.datarecoverysoftwarehelp.com/2012/01/30/thanks-to-efficient-file-recovery-software-for-recovering-formatted-files/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Jan 2012 09:57:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Data Recovery]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[deleted file recovery]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[file recovery]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[file recovery software]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[recover deleted files]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.datarecoverysoftwarehelp.com/?p=517</guid>
      <description>Almost every Windows user must have formatted his/her computer at least once. There could be various reasons behind formatting and some of the most common are virus infection, system unbootable, sluggish performance of system, etc. But, whatever be the cause of formatting the end result is loss of precious data.&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/data-recovery-software-help/Data_Recovery_Software_Help-Thanks_to_Efficient_File_Recovery_Software_For_Recovering_Formatted_Files.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><!-- p { margin-bottom: 0.21cm; } -->Almost every Windows user must have formatted his/her computer at least once. There could be various reasons behind formatting and some of the most common are virus infection, system unbootable, sluggish performance of system, etc. But, whatever be the cause of formatting the end result is loss of precious data. Therefore, it is always recommended specially to Windows users to maintain backup of their valuable data so that they can easily recover the loss. But, what do we do if we do not have the backup or insufficient backup? Well, for the users who do not have proper backup, there are bunch of file recovery<strong> </strong>software to recover valuable files or data. However, I too was quite unaware of the fact that recovery of formatted files is possible through third-party recovery software before I encountered the situation.</p>
<p>Let me explain you my case in detail.</p>
<p>For the past few days I was very much perturbed with the sluggish performance of my Windows XP based laptop. Scanned all the drives and even entire system for three times with the latest anti-virus but the problem persisted. However, the situation became jittery when my laptop denied restarting after running virus scan for the fourth time. Worried, restarted it for many times but with no luck. However, without losing hope inserted Windows XP installation disk to repair system from Recovery Console but didn’t find any solution. That situation left me nothing but to format the hard disk of my laptop and reinstall Windows XP OS.</p>
<p>Although I was having the backup of almost all of the data on external hard disk but there were some really very crucial doc files present on the My Document which were not backed up. Losing those files would be a big loss as they were containing my latest work which I had not submitted to my boss. However, at that time the immediate importance was formatting the hard disk. Thus, I formatted my laptop and then put the issue of losing files due to formatting in front of IT Support of my office. A member from IT Support team came and took my laptop with him and after few hours called me to their room.</p>
<p>I was shocked to see all the formatted files on the interface of some file recovery software. This was something very strange which I could believe as I was not at all aware of the fact that recovery of formatted files or data is possible. However, then I pointed out few of the formatted files of which I didn’t backed up and in few minutes the software recovered all the required ones. Thus, after successfully recovering all my files I asked that person from IT Support about that file recovery software.</p>
<p>He told me that he used <a href="http://www.stellarinfo.com/file-recovery.htm"><strong>Stellar Phoenix File Recovery</strong></a> software<strong> </strong>to recover all the formatted files. Further, he told me that Stellar Phoenix File Recovery software is one of the finest file recovery tools which uses high-end scanning algorithms for recovery of lost, formatted, or deleted files. The software has different versions for Mac and Windows users and supports recovery of 185 file types including emails, photos, videos, text documents, etc. Thus, to protect my data from future mishaps, I downloaded this efficient tool. <strong> </strong></p>
